High engagement rate driven by strong CTR. Carousel format performed exceptionally well.

Eid Mubarak greeting carousel. Exceptional organic engagement rate (30.5%) and strong CTR (21.5%) demonstrate strong community resonance with cultural recognition content. High engagement from pharmacy professionals celebrating Eid validates inclusive messaging approach.

Ishpal testimonial - part of The Titan Way campaign. Strong organic engagement rate (12.8%) and CTR (8.3%) demonstrate effective testimonial messaging. Key quote '20 minutes in the dispensary' resonates strongly with pharmacist audience seeking time freedom. Video performance: 196 views with 11s average watch time. Testimonial effectively communicates workflow transformation and time reclamation for clinical services.

The Titan Way main campaign video - exceptional organic performance with 20.2% engagement rate and 14.9% CTR. Strong video metrics: 1,539 views with 12s average watch time. Sponsored boost ran 27-31 March with lower engagement (0.1%) but significant reach amplification. High-quality comments from pharmacy professionals validate messaging. This video serves as the campaign hero asset explaining the complete Titan Way workflow transformation.

The Titan Way looped video - campaign launch post. Strong organic engagement rate (15.7%) and CTR (9.1%) demonstrate effective messaging. Sponsored boost ran 27-29 March with lower engagement (0.3%) but higher reach. Video performance: 550 views with 9s average watch time. Visual metaphor of papers clearing to reveal Kanban board effectively communicates workflow transformation.

Exceptional engagement rate (67.8%) and click-through rate (61.6%) demonstrate strong community resonance with the charitable cause. High conversion to page views and followers indicates compelling call-to-action.

Elias paperless testimonial. Good engagement rate (6.9%) and video performance (438 views, 9s average watch time, 56.8% view rate). Strong repost rate (3) and comments (2) indicate message resonates with pharmacy community.

Growth positioning carousel. Exceptional engagement rate (41.4%) and CTR (40.0%) with 342 clicks, indicating strong message resonance and high intent. High click volume suggests strong interest in The Titan Way solution.

Anup testimonial about The Titan Way. Strong engagement rate (13.2%) and CTR (9.4%) with excellent video performance (406 views, 14s average watch time, 51% view rate). High reaction count (26) and comments (2) indicate strong message resonance.

First look at TITAN merch in the wild. Strong performance with 12.3% engagement rate, 9.8% CTR, and excellent video metrics (1,421 views, 17s average watch time, 73.5% view rate). High comment count (7) and reposts (6) indicate strong community engagement.

The Titan Way positioning post using emotional appeal. Low impressions (322) but decent engagement rate (5.0%) suggests message resonates with those who see it. Limited reach indicates potential for broader distribution.

Influencer-style video promoting TITAN Merch Store. Good engagement rate (8.5%) and video performance (310 views, 13s average watch time, 43% view rate). Strong repost rate (4) indicates message resonates and is being shared.

Independent pharmacy advocacy carousel. Exceptional engagement rate (46.8%) and CTR (45.1%) with 658 clicks, indicating strong community mobilization and high intent to take action. High repost rate (6) suggests message is being shared widely.

TITAN Merch Store launch carousel. Exceptional organic performance with 70.4% engagement rate and 67.9% CTR, indicating strong community interest. High click volume (1,097 clicks) suggests strong intent to visit store. Sponsored campaign ran 3/6-3/12 with 2,383 additional impressions.
The Titan Way looped video. Strong engagement rate (7.1%) and CTR (5.5%) with good video performance (374 views, 12s average watch time). Visual design successfully draws attention to workflow.
Kanav testimonial video about workflow efficiency. Strong video performance (449 views, 14s average watch time) and decent CTR (4.2%) indicate content resonates with target audience.
The Titan Way positioning post addressing workflow inefficiencies. Moderate engagement rate (4.6%) with 1 follower gained indicates message resonates with target audience.
Ramadan greeting carousel with English and Arabic versions. Strong engagement rate (23.1%) and high CTR (18.7%) indicate strong community resonance.

Organic post. Pop culture visual reference (Space Odyssey) effectively communicated transformation and innovation positioning. Comments from industry professionals (Balal Anwar, Meditech UK) validated 'TITAN PMR way' brand positioning. Good engagement (9.3% engagement rate, 7.1% CTR) and strong comments (9 comments) validate brand positioning approach.

Organic post. Testimonial effectively communicated paperless benefits and workflow efficiency. Cameron's authentic experience resonated with audience. Good engagement (8.5% engagement rate, 6.6% CTR) and strong watch time (13 seconds average) indicate strong audience interest in testimonial content. Discussion prompt didn't generate comments despite good engagement.

Organic post. Exceptional performance: 55.7% engagement rate, 54.3% CTR. Timeline format effectively communicated pharmacy evolution and TITAN's role at each stage. Content successfully positioned TITAN as thought leader in pharmacy evolution. Discussion prompt didn't generate broader conversation despite good engagement.

Organic post. Product demonstration through real pharmacy team members effectively communicated workflow features and automation benefits. Good engagement (7.8% engagement rate, 5.8% CTR) and strong watch time (18 seconds average) indicate strong audience interest in product demonstration content. Discussion prompt didn't generate comments despite good engagement.

Organic post. Visual animation format effectively communicated legacy PMR pain points (excessive printing, chaos, outdated behavior). Good engagement (8.9% engagement rate, 6.8% CTR) and strong watch time (10 seconds average) indicate strong audience interest. Comments from Aron Garner and Balal Anwar validated innovation positioning.

Organic post. 'From day one' messaging and new pharmacy positioning resonated with audience. Good engagement (7.0% engagement rate, 5.2% CTR) and strong watch time (12 seconds average) indicate strong audience interest in new pharmacy setup content. Comment from Kanav Sikka himself validated message and provided social proof.

Organic post. Positioning content that differentiates TITAN as innovator from legacy PMRs as imitators. Visual concept (split lightbulb) effectively communicated differentiation. Good engagement (7.5% engagement rate, 5.6% CTR) validates positioning approach. Discussion prompt didn't generate broader conversation despite good engagement.

Organic post. Exceptional performance: 53.4% engagement rate, 51.8% CTR. Reframing messaging resonated strongly with audience frustration. Content successfully reframed pharmacy challenges by positioning legacy PMRs as the problem, not pharmacies themselves. Discussion prompt encouraged comments including strong testimonial from Owen Keil that validated message and provided social proof.

Organic post. Visual animation format engaged solution providers and partnership-minded stakeholders. Discussion prompt ('What's the biggest bottleneck slowing you down?') encouraged 8 comments, demonstrating the value of including prompts in content. Strong engagement from solution providers (ClinicRx, Balal Anwar, Cyrus Hodivala) suggests partnership opportunities.

Organic post. Strong performance: 23.2% engagement rate, 21.6% CTR. Milestone announcement celebrating EPS full rollout across Wales. Features government endorsement through Eluned Morgan MS quote, demonstrating NHS alignment and innovation leadership. Bilingual messaging (English and Welsh) demonstrated cultural sensitivity and local relevance.

Organic post. Waiting times messaging and team member perspective resonated with audience. Good engagement (7.6% engagement rate, 5.9% CTR) and strong watch time (11 seconds average) indicate strong audience interest in efficiency improvements. Testimonial from pharmacy team member (not owner) adds authenticity and relatability.

Organic post. Service expansion messaging and 'since day one' positioning resonated with audience. Good engagement (8.0% engagement rate, 6.3% CTR) and strong watch time (13 seconds average) indicate strong audience interest in service expansion solutions. Multiple services mentioned (weight management, travel health, Pharmacy First, earwax removal) increased relatability.

Organic post. Educational explainer content  strong engagement from solution providers and partnership-minded stakeholders. Positioned TITAN as AI-first without hype  clear feature-to-outcome logic. Visual infographic format performed well for saves and revisits. Comments from ClinicRx suggest partnership opportunities.

Post boosted from 2025-02-12 to 2025-02-13. Exceptional performance: 63.7% engagement rate, 62.4% CTR. High signal asset  NHS alignment + future-facing innovation. Social proof from NHS leadership (comments from Ghulam Haydar, Wasim Baqir) boosted confidence and credibility. Strong engagement from policy / tech stakeholders vs typical pharmacist-only audience.

Organic post. Poll results reveal time & staffing shortages (47%) as primary barrier to service expansion, validating messaging around time-saving and efficiency benefits. Limited participation (15 votes) suggests polls may need more active promotion. Results influence future content strategy toward service enablement messaging.

Organic post. Exceptional performance: 48.4% engagement rate, 46.9% CTR. Social proof through Trustpilot reviews from real pharmacy owners built trust and credibility effectively. Real customer testimonials validated product quality and addressed concerns. The exceptional engagement demonstrates extremely high audience interest in social proof content.

Organic post. Strong scaling message ('50 patients at a time') and efficiency gains resonated with audience. Good engagement (8.5% engagement rate, 7.4% CTR) and strong watch time (15 seconds average) indicate strong audience interest in scaling solutions. The message about scaling without increasing man hours addressed a core concern for pharmacy owners.

Organic post. Strong product demonstration through motion graphics conveyed capability without needing on-camera testimonial. Mobile workflow resonates with remote working pharmacists and owners scaling services. Good engagement (6.1% engagement rate, 4.9% CTR) and strong watch time (18 seconds average) indicate strong audience interest. Positive feedback from ClinicRx praising platform as 'work of art' validates product quality.

Organic post. Exceptional performance: 24.4% engagement rate, 22.9% CTR. This carousel leaned heavily on quantified safety proof (500 near misses prevented daily), which is consistently high-performing and trust-building for pharmacists. The stat-driven angle and clear CTA likely drove the exceptional click-through rate.

Post boosted from 2025-01-22 to 2025-01-23. Strong organic performance (4.6% engagement rate, 2.7% CTR) but limited sponsored engagement (0.1% engagement rate). ROI framing (3K/month) and clear visual chart resonated with warm audience. Revenue numbers drive curiosity and stop-scroll. Reposts (5) indicate content was valuable for sharing.

Organic post. Strong performance: 8.9% engagement rate, 8.1% CTR, 16-second average watch time. Strong statistic headline (20%) and NHS priorities messaging resonated. Testimonial validated the 'free pharmacists for NHS priorities' narrative. Good engagement indicates strong audience interest in efficiency and delegation benefits.

Post boosted from 2025-01-20 to 2025-01-21. Exceptional performance: 45.5% total engagement rate (48.9% organic), 45.0% CTR (48.1% organic). Educational carousel format resonated strongly with audience. Better sponsored performance (20.3% engagement rate) than previous feature-focused campaigns. High click-through indicates content was valuable and worth exploring.

Post boosted from 2025-01-17 to 2025-01-18. Strong organic performance (5.5% engagement rate, 3.7% CTR) but sponsored spend (291.76) delivered minimal uplift - only 51 impressions with 0 engagements. Unusually high eCPM indicates inefficient spend. Feature-focused ads convert poorly without warm touchpoint.

Organic post. Strong engagement (7.5% engagement rate, 6.2% CTR) indicates high interest. Reinforces private services narrative and pairs effectively with poll results showing expanding private services as priority.

Post boosted from 2025-01-20 to 2025-01-22. Strong organic performance (53.3% engagement rate, 51.8% CTR). Sponsored added 449 impressions with 38 engagements. High click-throughs indicate interest in automation partners.

Organic poll. Results validate private services growth narrative with 73% voting for expanding private services. High click rate (4.0% CTR) indicates strong interest. Limited reach due to algorithmic throttling of polls compared to other content types.
Organic post. Strong impressions and engagement for policy content demonstrates appetite for NHS-aligned context. No comments despite discussion invite.
Organic post. Strong CTR (5.7%) and watch time (12 seconds) indicate high engagement. Emotional storytelling and measurable results (NMS 30180) drive conversion potential.
Post boosted from 2025-01-15 to 2025-01-17. All engagement came from organic traffic. Sponsored impressions achieved branding impact but no conversions.
Metrics to be populated after campaign launch. Success metric: impressions (target 5000+). Engagement rate will be inflated for carousels due to swipe counting.
